    "body": "## Problem\n\nAfter ad4bc2d90c5109c24bf6f0119ad31276f1518c6f, syntax highlight don't work after restart. \n\n## Steps to reproduce\ncd to neovim repro, run `nvim`, then `:e runtime/lua/vim/F.lua | mks! /tmp/sess.vim | restart exe \"au FileType * quit\" | so /tmp/sess.vim`\n\nNotice no syntax highlight after restart, since no FileType.\n\n## Expected behavior\nFileType should happened when source Session.vim.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2727 gad4bc2d90c` neovim/neovim@ad4bc2d90c\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.9-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
